<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="appoint-vt">appoint <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əˈpɔɪnt/    美 /əˈpɔɪnt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>任命；委派：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>appoint sb (as) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sam has been appointed manager of the engineering department to take the place of George.
山姆被任命为工程部经理，接替乔治。</p><footer>2012 重庆</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>appoint sb to sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has been appointed to the committee.
他已被派到委员会任职。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>appoint sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A nurse was appointed to guard her.
一名护士被委派来守护她。</p><footer>2014 浙江改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>指定；约定：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We appointed a day in June for celebration.
我们把庆祝会定在六月的一天。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everyone has assembled in the hall at the <strong>appointed time</strong>.
所有人都在指定时间到大厅里集合了。</p></div></div>